headline.main: Pistons Set Season High for Points in 136-106 Rout of 76ers
headline.print_headline: Pistons Set Season High for Points in 136-106 Rout of 76ers

lead_paragraph: Kentavious Caldwell-Pope scored 13 of his 26 points in Detroit's dominating third quarter, and the Pistons set a season high for points while rolling to a 136-106 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Saturday night.
